    "All these models should be regarded as com-plementary, and answering different questions.",
    "For example, models that impose QNM spectral predictions might miss deviations induced by the non-Kerr nature.",
    "Models that impose amplitudes predictions coming from binary inspirals may be biased if the orbital dynamics is not captured by quasicircular models (due to orbital eccentricity, precession, environmental effects etc.).",
    "In particular, the pSEOB class of templates, within its current implementation, is expected to be the most sensitive to deviations that abruptly appear around the merger phase, e.g.",
    "triggered by high-curvature dynamical couplings, similar to dynamical scalarisation [107]."
